
<section id="MidiConvert">
  <title>Converters</title>

  <para>
    The following opcodes can convert MIDI information. Some are conceived to
    work with a MIDI-triggered instrument instance. All opcodes converting from
    MIDI note to frequency (and back) use the global variable <link
    linkend="A4"><citetitle>A4</citetitle></link> to set the reference frequency
    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          MIDI note number to frequency converters (MIDI-triggered events):
          <link linkend="cpsmidi"><citetitle>cpsmidi</citetitle></link>,
          <link linkend="cpsmidib"><citetitle>cpsmidib</citetitle></link>,
          <link linkend="cpstmid"><citetitle>cpstmid</citetitle></link>,
          <link linkend="octmidi"><citetitle>octmidi</citetitle></link>,
          <link linkend="octmidib"><citetitle>octmidib</citetitle></link>,
          <link linkend="pchmidi"><citetitle>pchmidi</citetitle></link>,
          <link linkend="pchmidib"><citetitle>pchmidib</citetitle></link>.
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          MIDI note number to frequency converter (general case):
          <link linkend="mtof"><citetitle>mtof</citetitle></link>,
          <link linkend="cpsmidinn"><citetitle>cpsmidinn</citetitle></link>
        </para>
      </listitem>>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Pitch/frequency to MIDI note number converters: <link
          linkend="ftom"><citetitle>ftom</citetitle></link>, <link
          linkend="pchtom"><citetitle>pchtom</citetitle></link>.
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
        MIDI velocity to amplitude converters: <link
        linkend="ampmidi"><citetitle>ampmidi</citetitle></link>,
         <link linkend="ampmidid"><citetitle>ampmidid</citetitle></link> and
         <link linkend="ampmidicurve"><citetitle>ampmidicurve</citetitle></link>
        </para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Note name to midi / frequency and viceversa:
          <link linkend="ntom"><citetitle>ntom</citetitle></link>,
          <link linkend="mton"><citetitle>mton</citetitle></link>,
          <link linkend="ntof"><citetitle>ntof</citetitle></link>.
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
  </para>

</section>
